P!perms

Pancake APP

10/06/2024 at 22:04:04 GMT+1

The perms command works as follows: `p!perms [-u | -r | -c] [value] You can allow or or deny a specific command or an entire category by replacing with the command or category name. Adding -u <@user> after the permission, will allow or deny that permission for that specific user. Adding -r after the permission, will allow or deny that permission for that specific role. Adding -c <#channel> after the permission will allow or deny that permission for that specific channel. Not adding any options after the permission will allow or deny that permission for the entire server. If you wish to reset all perms, you can do so with p!perms reset. If you wish to set a perm back to default, you can do so with p!perms default . If you wish to list the perms that are specifically allowed or denied for the server, user, or role, do p!perms list [-u | -r] [value]. Examples: p!perms deny say p!perms allow say -u 80821761460928512 p!perms deny music p!perms allow music -r DJ p!perms allow mod -r Moderator p!perms list -r 297561578499342336 p!perms reset`

The perms command works as follows: `p!perms [-u | -r | -c] [value] You can allow or or deny a specific command or an entire category by replacing with the command or category name. Adding -u <@user> after the permission, will allow or deny that permission for that specific user. Adding -r after the permission, will allow or deny that permission for that specific role. Adding -c <#channel> after the permission will allow or deny that permission for that specific channel. Not adding any options after the permission will allow or deny that permission for the entire server. If you wish to reset all perms, you can do so with p!perms reset. If you wish to set a perm back to default, you can do so with p!perms default . If you wish to list the perms that are specifically allowed or denied for the server, user, or role, do p!perms list [-u | -r] [value]. Examples: p!perms deny say p!perms allow say -u 80821761460928512 p!perms deny music p!perms allow music -r DJ p!perms allow mod -r Moderator p!perms list -r 297561578499342336 p!perms reset`
